	   <tr><td colspan=2>Myself (now a 48 druid) and a 53 monk took this camp Friday night.<br>Easy (very easy) camp for the 2 of us, provided LD was not a factor. I had 2 LD deaths, but got rezzed.<br>Anyway, AM (or PH) spawns in front of the book case, and a Knight spawns just in front of him.<br>They are both on 30min timers (from our experience), and spread them apart by 5 min.<br>Best thing to do is pull back down the hall..nothing aggros in the hall. Just be careful of the hole with the ladder (drop for 253hp average) The corner is the best bet...Snare to be sure he cant run. and Debuff if there is a fire shield. Other than that, the knights are easy, the wizards can be tough (fire/magic/cold buffs) and the AM can be a pain if not alone.<br>When bored, monk would pull from the main hall for fun..good exp for me, few blues to a 53....<br>The downside is that for us, 42 hours of camping starting Friday night through Sunday night, we had 7 AM's spawn (3 Friday, 4 Saturday, 0 Sunday), we got 2 Silversilk Leggings and no Robe.<br>Very discouraged, and after helping someone beat the FG, and get the FBSS to drop, he promised to get us the robe. <br>While I have read that AM spawns average 1 for every 5, and drops average 1 for every 6, we were no where near the averages. out of 42 hours, that is 84 spawns, and in 84 spawns, we had him 7 times, which is almost 1 for every 12, and no robe for 7 spawns.<br>I hope others have better luck with this camp. I am supposed to help another friend get hers later this week. I hope I have better luck next time..&nbsp;&nbsp;= )<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Elder Sglanton An'Saol- 65 Storm Warden<br><br>Torvonnilous</td></tr>
